data.name: Grilled Tofu Skewers
data.quickTastyDescription: Deliciously marinated tofu skewers grilled to perfection, packed with flavor and great for any meal!
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.
Press the tofu for about 15 minutes to remove excess moisture, then cut it into 1-inch cubes.
Chop bell peppers and red onion into similar-sized pieces.
In a bowl, mix soy sauce, olive oil, garlic powder, and black pepper to create a marinade.
Add the tofu cubes to the marinade and let them soak for 10 minutes.
Thread the marinated tofu, bell peppers, and red onion onto the skewers alternately.
Place the skewers on the preheated grill and cook for about 10 minutes, turning occasionally, until grill marks appear and the veggies are slightly tender.
Remove from the grill and serve hot.
data.detailedName: Grilled Tofu Skewers with Bell Peppers and Onion
